Gameplay is smooth, I love the graphics, and the fact that there are no in app purchases. You can unlock everything by playing on once you buy the game. This is hands down a perfect successor to Swordigo. Totally worth every penny. The New Game Plus is also super amazing, adrenaline-pumping, challenging and frustrating but once you get to know the pattern, it's easier. This game puts your eye-hand combination to the limit. Controls are intuitive; best played with controller although I 100%ed it without using one. Cloud save is a nice topping. Overall an excellent 2.5D hack-and-slash game for Android. Good job Direlight. We want more of this!

This game is smooth as butter. With a simplistic yet satisfying control scheme, you slash and dash your way through enemies that feel good to kill with the right mix of challenge and fast pace. Obvious stylistic influences from Souls, and they do the style a service with this game. Character progression is paced perfectly and upgrades feel impactful. Limited but noticeably varying play styles with different build options. Too many good things to say; perfect cell phone game.

content: A very solid port of one of the best CRPG of all time. It looks fantastic even on small screen. The controls are accurate as far as my experience (playing it on my phone) is concern. Runs very smoothly and is pretty stable. They also add some little conveniences here and there that seasoned BG gamers would greatly appreciate. One thing that I wish they would incorporate is the ability to install the game on external SD card. As for the game itself, well it is the Baldur's Gate 2 as we know it, one of the best CRPG of all time. The gameplay depth and replayability, the moving narrative and flavorful story-telling, the confusing early ADnD ruleset are all here in their fullest glory. This is a BG fans dream come true. 5/5.
